Qualifications:
1. Two-year Associate degree in Paralegal or Legal Assistant Studies;
2. Eighteen months of Paralegal experience;
3. Any combination of training and experience that demonstrates experience in legal work, independent judgment, legal terminology principles, concepts, systems, and processes. Experience must include discovery and trial methods and procedures, legal ethics, and skill in preparing legal documents, interviewing witnesses, and explaining legal issues.

